Reasoning: The paper discusses fundamental relations between formal systems, algorithms, and dynamical systems, with a focus on undecidability, universality, diagonalization, and self-reference. These topics are relevant to several subfields of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of Cellular Automata (CAs) in distributed computation, which could also place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. However, given the emphasis on undecidability and self-reference, we believe that cs.LO and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories.
